    <div class="post-grid">
      <article class="post-content">
        <p class="lede-p"><strong>Screaming Frog is the desktop crawler nearly every technical SEO has on their laptop.</strong> It is also a tool that exposes problems without fixing any of them, generates reports nobody reads, and quietly turns into a $259/yr line item that justifies itself once a quarter. After 30 days inside the free and paid versions — plus interviews with 12 paying users across in-house, agency, and freelance contexts — here is the honest 2026 verdict, where the free version is enough, and what to do once you have the audit report.</p>

